benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: The test suite includes scenarios for default retrieval and multiple parameterized requests, ensuring valid GET behavior.
Empty Response: Tests TC11 and TC29 verify system behavior when no queue entries exist or filters exclude all data.

Query Parameters: Tests cover multiple query parameters (accountId, queueName, serviceName, minDate, maxDate) and combinations (all filters) including withHistory, withInProcessing, withBusEvents, withNotifications, and handling of extra/unexpected parameters.
Authorization: There is an Unauthorized access test (TC15) ensuring proper error handling for missing/invalid tokens.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination for large datasets.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover how the system handles multiple requests in a short time.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers).
recommendations: Add pagination tests to ensure proper handling of large datasets (page size, page navigation).
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under bursty traffic.
Add caching behavior tests to verify caching headers and invalidation on data changes.
Add explicit authorization/forbidden tests (403) and token expiry scenarios for stronger access control coverage.
